The paper deals with the problem of unsupervised multi-view feature selection, which involves learning a similarity structure from multiple views of data. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Given that the paper proposes a novel approach to learning a collaborative similarity structure for feature selection, it is likely to be of interest to researchers in these sub-fields.
